Chapter/Unit-3 Pod scheduling
==============================

Pod scheduling in Kubernetes is the process of assigning a pod to a node in the cluster. The Kube-scheduler is responsible for selecting a suitable node based on resource availability, constraints, and scheduling policies.

Q) How Does Kubernetes Schedule Pods?
Q) 
Note: Pod scheduling are 4 types
			1) Node name based pod scheduling
			2) Name label and Pod selecter based
			3) Taint and tolerations
			4) Affinity and Anti-affinity rules.

1) Node name based Pod scheduling
================================
 => It does not matter the health of node. pod will run as per node which you have defined.
 => Not use in companies, because we can put only one name at a time and in case if node went down then scheduler will not run your pod on different node.(does not provide fail-over)
 => Only Node based scheduling work in case if scheduling went down. and rest scheduling techonology will not work.

