3) Taint and tolerations
=========================
 => In Kubernetes, taints and tolerations are used to control the scheduling of pods into nodes in a cluster.
 => They help to ensure that only certain pods are placed on specific nodes, based on specific conditions and requirements.

 For this we have two rules
 1) taint: node side
 2) tolerations: deployment side.

Each taint consists of three parts:
  => Key: The key represents the name of the taint and is used to uniquely identify it.
  => Value: An optional value associated with the taint key.
  => Effect: The effect determines how the taint affects pod scheduling.


